law.text:
A person is guilty of aggressive driving if the person commits three or more of the following offenses at the same time or during a single and continuous period of driving in violation of:
§ 21-202 of this title (Traffic lights with steady indication);
§ 21-303 of this title (Overtaking and passing vehicles);
§ 21-304 of this title (Passing on right);
§ 21-309 of this title (Driving on laned roadways);
§ 21-310 of this title (Following too closely);
§ 21-403 of this title (Failure to yield right-of-way); or
§ 21-801.1 of this title (Exceeding a maximum speed limit or posted maximum speed limit).
